-- Airbus confirms A330-200 crashed in Libya
-- 
-- Wed May 12, 2010 4:24am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/05/12/us-crash-libya-airbus-idUSTRE64B1H520100512

 

 PARIS  (Reuters) - European planemaker Airbus ( EAD.PA ) confirmed that a passenger plane that crashed in Libya on Wednesday was an Airbus A330-200 operated by Afriqiyah Airways arriving from Johannesburg. 

 "Airbus will provide full technical assistance to the authorities responsible for the investigation into the accident through the Bureau d'Enquete et d'Analyse (BEA)," Airbus said in a statement. (Reporting by  James Regan )